  "prompt": "If you were born deaf, what language would you think in?",
  "response": "If someone is born deaf and does not have exposure to spoken language, they may develop a way of thinking that is visual or conceptual rather than based on spoken words. This could include thinking in images, concepts, or through sign language if they are exposed to it. People who are deaf often develop rich inner lives and modes of thought that do not rely on auditory language, and their thinking can be influenced by their experiences, culture, and access to different forms of communication. Ultimately, the way one thinks is highly individual and can vary widely from person to person.",
